Oatmeal Breakfast Cookies
  --Heilala Vanilla

1 large packed c pitted dates
1/3 c boiling water
1 egg
3 tbsp vanilla syrup
3 tbsp coconut oil, melted
1 tsp vanilla powder
1 1/4 c rolled oats
1/2 c flaked almonds
1/4 c desiccated coconut
1/2 c sunflower seeds or chopped nuts of your choice
1/4 c raisins
3/4 c almond meal
1/2 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp cinnamon

Pre-heat oven to 350F. Line a tray with baking paper. Roughly chop dates. Place in bowl, pour over boiling water. Cover and leave to soak for 10 min then mash to a paste. Add syrup, coconut oil, lightly beaten egg and vanilla and mix to combine. Add dry ingredients (oats, almonds, coconut, sunflower seeds, raisins, almond meal, baking powder & cinnamon) and mix together until well combined to a thick batter. Measure out heaped tbsp of mix and shape to a thick flattened round. Place on lined tray and bake 20 min until golden. Remove from oven, leave to cool on tray. Keep for 5 days in an airtight container.
